\c 3
\s1 King Nebucadnezar's golden statue
\p
\v 1 King Nebucadnezar ordered for a idol statue to be built with a height of 2,7 meters and a width of 3 meters. This statue was to be set/put in the plains of Dura in the province of Babylonia.
\v 2Then the king sent an invitation to all the governors, regency heads, state advisors, treasurer's, judges, law experts and other high ranking officials to attend the dedication of the idol statue that was built by King Nebucadnezar.
\v 3 After they all had gathered and stood before the idol statue for the dedication
\v 4 an announcer made an announcement with a very loud voice, To everyone from every tribe, nation and language, this is the king's order,
